definition:
Someone descended from Pallu who was a man of the tribe of Reuben living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.9; 
 son of: Reuben (H7205); 
 brother of: Hanoch (H2585J), Hezron (H2696) and Carmi (H3756); 
 father of: Eliab (H0446H)
Group of pal.lu (פַּלּוּא "Pallu" H6396) 
 § Palluites, of Pallu "wonderful"
 descendants of Pallu, the 2nd son of Reuben
